Option 1: Merge remote changes into your local branch
#git checkout main
#git pull origin main   # brings remote changes into local main
#git push origin main   # now push your local commits

Option 2: Force overwrite remote (⚠️ destructive)
If you’re absolutely sure you want your local code to completely replace what’s on GitHub:
#git push origin main --force
⚠️ Warning: This will discard any commits that exist on the remote main but not in your local branch.
Only use this if you know the remote history isn’t needed.

Option 3: Push master directly into main
If your local master branch has the code you want, and you want to overwrite remote main:
#git push origin master:main --force
This pushes your local master branch into the remote main branch.